{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EPdJoyTTJz9Po3uXnGN593","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the bug clearly. The original code:\n\n1. **Backend (handler.go)**: The `promptFile` struct didn't have a `Contents` field - it only had `Path` and `History`. So the API only returned the git commit history, not the file contents.\n\n2. **Frontend (project_detail.html)**: The original code rendered `pf.history` (the git commits) when expanding the details, showing SHA, date, and message for each commit.\n\nThe fix has already been applied in the working directory (the diffs show the changes), but these are unstaged changes. The fix:\n1. Added `Contents string` to the `promptFile` struct\n\n\n2. Added logic to read the file contents from disk\n3. Changed the frontend to show `pf.contents` instead of `pf.history`\n\nSo the fix is already in place in the working tree. The user mentioned a permissions issue about approving a write to `.cloche/prompts/update-docs.md`, which seems separate from the main bug fix that's already been implemented.\n\nThe actual task is to fix the bug where clicking expansion arrows in the Prompts section shows git commits instead of file contents, and looking at the diff, that fix has already been partially applied. Now I need to verify the indentation in the handler.go changes is correct—the lines after `contents := \"\"` look misaligned, though Go will still compile regardless. Let me check if this actually works as intended. The fix looks solid—the backend now reads file contents from disk and exposes them through a `Contents` field, while the frontend displays that instead of the git history. There's some dead code in the `toggleDiff` function that's no longer being called, but that's not causing the bug. Let me verify this compiles correctly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5